'''Holt Kazed''', also rendered '''holt kazet''', was the term used by the [[Nelvaanian/Legends|Nelvaanians]] for the heroic individual known as '''Ghost Hand''', who legend said would come during a time of great need. The Nelvaanians believed that [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] was the Holt Kazed, due to his mechanical hand, which he wore during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]].

According to the legend, the Holt Kazed was a warrior who would lose his hand in battle with a [[Dooku/Legends|great beast or monster]], but who would then receive a new one that would grant him [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|great power]]. With this power, the warrior would be able to defeat any enemy. The Holt Kazed, it was prophesied, would come to the Nelvaanian people in a time of great hardship and sorrow, when nature herself (the [[Great Mother]] planet) would be hurt, or violently thrown out of balance by a great illness—which ultimately the hero would heal. But the legend had a dark, ominous side to it, as it foretold that the warrior's power would increase mightily to the point where it would overpower him, [[Great Jedi Purge/Legends|kill]] [[Jedi Order/Legends|his friends]], [[Padmé Amidala/Legends|strangle his loved ones]], and, eventually, [[Duel on Mustafar/Legends|utterly]] [[Darth Vader's armor/Legends|consume]] the hero himself. The legend is told through a vision that Anakin Skywalker experiences during his journey in trying to heal the Great Mother. If carefully studied, it becomes clear that the legend of Holt Kazed is actually a foretelling of Anakin's eventual transformation into the Sith Lord, [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] Vader.

